REACH Essentials Toothbrushes also come with a contoured handle made of soft rubber and plastic for a comfortable cushion grip that’s easy to hold and control. Includes 6 toothbrushes with toothbrush covers to protect the bristles. Great for the entire family, these toothbrushes will consistently help maintain oral hygiene daily. Don't just brush, REACH!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are awesome
reviews.reviewText: I bought some brushes at BJ’s and each lady like a week and then my faith in the future of humankind’s teeth was restored when I received my reach toothbrushes. They are AWESOME! They clean thoroughly, are durable and the little covers they include make them perfect for travel! Keep it up Reach!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality toothbrushes
reviews.reviewText: I bought a pack from Walmart (another brand) and they were only good for a couple weeks before they started falling part. These are much better quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Does A Good Job At Its Purpose At A Good Price
reviews.reviewText: I got these over the Basics because these were available in the medium style over soft. The handle is ergonomic and easy to grip. The bristles are nice and medium, like I like. I tried the tongue scrapper, but I probably won't use it consistently. It's good to know it's there though.One brush was missing the cap, but I let that slide since I don't intend on traveling with it. I'd honestly only need one anyway. The bag is a resealable Ziplock style. The colors are kind of feminine, all light shades of blue, aqua, green, grey, purple and orange. I won't want to use these around my guy buddies.Overall, you can't beat the value at ~67 cents per.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice for the price
reviews.reviewText: This toothbrush is a little awkward in the hand. It also has very stiff bristles, though it is a Medium. On the other hand, it does the job and doesn't cost as much as most others.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute and effective
reviews.reviewText: They’re toothbrushes, they do what they’re supposed to, very well. This specific pack is the one I always buy now. They’re pretty and I love the caps too, I don’t have to worry about putting my toothbrush down and it picking something up.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: These toothbrushes are great value for money, but are very stiff and hard. I would classify them as firm or hard bristles. I do not tend to have sensitive gums but when I brush with these like I do normally, my gums bleed. Would not recommend for someone who has sensitive gums. Also, only 4 toothbrushes come with a cover, not all of them.
